Create a Virtual Environment (virutal env will be specific to python version used)
Manage a Virtual Environment
Manage packages with pip


https://www.liquidweb.com/kb/how-to-setup-a-python-virtual-environment-on-centos/
        what to install to create virtual env
        on Fedora
            $dnf install python3-virtualenv
            $ python -m venv new_virt
            $ 
        on Centos
            $ sudo tum update -y
            $ sudo python3 -m venv python3-virtualenv
            $ source python3.8-virtualenv/bin/activate
            $ yum install python3.8-pip
            $ pip3 freeze ( Output installed packages in requirements format)
        Installing packages using pip
            $ pip install -r requirements.txt (where requirements.txt have list of packages and their versions)
            



